    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Gas detector activated and platform alarm sounded",
      "Personnel mustered at muster station",
      "Production Supervisor and Day Lead Operator responded to assess leak",
      "All clear given at 0941 hours",
      "Workers showered and reported to sickbay",
      "Medical examination via telemedicine",
      "Both workers cleared and released to full duty",
      "Safety stand-down ordered"
    ],
    "summary": "On 10 May 2023 at approximately 0930 hours, two Grand Isle Shipyard workers were removing bolts from a flange on a 2-inch Well Equalization Header line during a scheduled shut-in at MC 941 Platform A (Titan spar). When loosening the last bolt, trapped pressure from residual fluids in a dog leg bend above the flange was released, spraying both workers in the face with hydrocarbon fluid. A nearby gas detector activated at 0933 hours, triggering platform alarm and muster. No injuries, pollution, or equipment damage occurred. Workers were wearing safety glasses and face shields which prevented injury. Investigation found that the possibility of residual fluids/trapped pressure in the dog leg bend was overlooked despite completion of Simple Isolation Certificate and zero pressure indication on gauge.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Review isolations to look for any possibility of hydrocarbon release from doglegs or dead-legs due to residual fluid static pressure remaining after lockout/tagout is completed, even if zero pressure is indicated on the gauge",
      "Implement engineering controls for residual fluids or static pressure release",
      "Review isolations for potential hydrocarbon release from dog-legs or dead-legs even when gauge indicates zero pressure",
      "Utilize appropriate engineering controls for personnel safety"
    ],
    "key_phrases": [
      "trapped pressure",
      "residual fluids",
      "dog leg bend",
      "overlooked",
      "zero pressure indicated on gauge",
      "Simple Isolation Certificate",
      "lockout/tagout",
      "hydrocarbon release"
    ]
  },
